Here, this, this way!

39
00:04:28,270 --> 00:04:29,860
Down there! There!

40
00:04:29,860 --> 00:04:32,080
- What's going on? 
 - Oh, my.

41
00:04:32,080 --> 00:04:34,510
What's going on?

42
00:04:38,120 --> 00:04:39,850
Oh my!

43
00:04:39,850 --> 00:04:41,290
What happened?

44
00:04:41,290 --> 00:04:43,010
What's that?

45
00:04:49,340 --> 00:04:53,020
Oh, Ro Na! What happened to you?

46
00:04:54,950 --> 00:04:57,120
Ro Na!

47
00:05:00,630 --> 00:05:04,400
Ro Na, Ro Na, please open your eyes! Why are you like this?

48
00:05:04,400 --> 00:05:07,560
You're scaring me. Please open your eyes! What's wrong, Sweetie?

49
00:05:07,560 --> 00:05:09,070
Put her down, down, huh?

50
00:05:09,070 --> 00:05:12,700
Do something! Please!

51
00:05:14,880 --> 00:05:17,610
Please help my child!

52
00:05:17,610 --> 00:05:20,230
Ro Na!

53
00:05:20,230 --> 00:05:21,750
Hey, Ro Na! Can you hear me?

54
00:05:21,750 --> 00:05:23,390
You've got to stay awake!

55
00:05:23,390 --> 00:05:25,850
Ambulance! Ambulance, quickly!

56
00:05:25,850 --> 00:05:28,490
Hurry, hurry!

57
00:05:28,490 --> 00:05:30,420
Hello? Yes.

58
00:05:30,420 --> 00:05:32,010
Send an ambulance immediately. Please hurry!

59
00:05:32,010 --> 00:05:33,740
We're at Cheong Ah Arts School.

60
00:05:33,740 --> 00:05:35,630
A child is hurt. A child

61
00:05:35,630 --> 00:05:38,140
is losing a lot of blood—

62
00:05:39,040 --> 00:05:40,450
Ro Na!

63
00:05:40,450 --> 00:05:41,560
Oh my, Ro Na!

64
00:05:41,560 --> 00:05:44,300
Min Hyeok. Min Hyeok!

65
00:05:44,300 --> 00:05:47,090
No, no!

66
00:05:47,090 --> 00:05:49,660
Don't worry. She's going to be okay.

67
00:05:49,660 --> 00:05:50,800
Don't look.

68
00:05:50,800 --> 00:05:52,980
She has no pulse, and she isn't breathing.

69
00:05:52,980 --> 00:05:54,000
Step back, back!

70
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:56,120
- Someone  killed her. 
 - Ro Na

71
00:06:01,510 --> 00:06:03,130
Ro Na, please!

72
00:06:03,200 --> 00:06:07,500
This- a homicide. Isn't this murder?

73
00:06:07,500 --> 00:06:10,440
Shut up! My daughter isn't dead.

74
00:06:10,440 --> 00:06:13,070
Why should my Ro Na be dead?

75
00:06:13,070 --> 00:06:15,060
Ro Na is still warm!

76
00:06:15,060 --> 00:06:18,860
She's still warm!

77
00:06:20,140 --> 00:06:22,120
Close the school gate right now!

78
00:06:22,120 --> 00:06:26,220
Stop anyone from leaving  until the police gets here!

79
00:06:26,220 --> 00:06:31,140
None of you will take even a single step until the police arrives!

80
00:06:31,140 --> 00:06:33,980
What are you doing, not closing the school gate?

81
00:06:35,710 --> 00:06:37,260
Yes!

82
00:06:40,160 --> 00:06:42,270
What's this noise?

83
00:06:46,080 --> 00:06:47,750
Fire! Fire!

84
00:06:47,750 --> 00:06:50,980
Teacher, Students!

85
00:06:52,750 --> 00:06:55,380
There's a person down here!

86
00:06:56,540 --> 00:06:58,760
No, my baby!

87
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:01,460
No!

88
00:07:03,120 --> 00:07:04,710
What about Eun Byeol? Didn't she go with you to the back?

89
00:07:04,710 --> 00:07:05,950
I said not to leave!

90
00:07:05,950 --> 00:07:09,000
Where did the fire break out?

91
00:07:11,120 --> 00:07:12,900
No!

92
00:07:14,250 --> 00:07:17,120
No!

93
00:07:27,000 --> 00:07:30,020
Will she be okay?

94
00:07:30,020 --> 00:07:33,750
I'll meet you up as soon as I can bring some order to the scene.

95
00:07:33,750 --> 00:07:36,390
You'll be okay, right?

96
00:07:37,810 --> 00:07:39,950
Hurry and go!

97
00:07:39,950 --> 00:07:42,110
 911 Emergency Vehicle  

98
00:08:07,140 --> 00:08:09,050
Be careful not to touch a thing.

99
00:08:09,050 --> 00:08:11,700
Anything can be evidence.

100
00:08:37,790 --> 00:08:39,400
Who is it there?

101
00:08:39,400 --> 00:08:40,930
Aren't you hungry?

102
00:08:40,930 --> 00:08:43,190
Can I get you anything?

103
00:08:44,260 --> 00:08:46,730
No, I don't want anything.

104
00:08:47,730 --> 00:08:49,610
How come did you lock the door?

105
00:08:49,610 --> 00:08:51,190
Are you in a bad mood?

106
00:08:51,190 --> 00:08:55,130
I said I didn't need anything! I'm fine!

107
00:08:58,240 --> 00:09:00,370
I just need to rest a little.

108
00:09:00,370 --> 00:09:03,220
I'm just exhausted.

109
00:09:03,220 --> 00:09:06,970
Okay. Get some rest then.

110
00:09:52,510 --> 00:09:54,670
No, no.

111
00:11:02,390 --> 00:11:04,480
- Check the blood!
 - Here we go.

112
00:11:04,480 --> 00:11:07,200
Get the defibrillator ready. Charge it to 120 joule.

113
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:08,920
Shot!

114
00:11:18,120 --> 00:11:20,010
No.

115
00:11:24,050 --> 00:11:26,700
Get the operating room open immediately and get a hold of the Neurosurgery Unit!

116
00:11:26,700 --> 00:11:28,980
Quick, get her to the operating room!

117
00:11:37,180 --> 00:11:40,750
Mommy is sorry. I was wrong, Ro Na!

118
00:11:41,290 --> 00:11:43,810
Don't leave me!

119
00:12:01,610 --> 00:12:03,480
Did anything come up?

120
00:12:03,480 --> 00:12:05,450
So many people rushed out all at once.

121
00:12:05,450 --> 00:12:09,580
In fact, it's going to be difficult to locate unique footprints and other evidence.

122
00:12:13,360 --> 00:12:15,790
How long are they going to keep us in here?

123
00:12:15,790 --> 00:12:17,370
We're busy people, you know!

124
00:12:17,370 --> 00:12:19,200
If she were your daughter, would you say the same?

125
00:12:19,200 --> 00:12:22,140
Someone would think she's your biological daughter.

126
00:12:22,140 --> 00:12:25,920
What makes you feel so guilty that you want to run away without getting questioned? You're hiding something, right?

127
00:12:25,920 --> 00:12:27,970
What did you just say?

128
00:12:27,970 --> 00:12:29,180
Seriously!

129
00:12:29,180 --> 00:12:31,140
Come on, you're an assemblyman. Do something!

130
00:12:31,140 --> 00:12:33,670
Hey! Let go!

131
00:12:33,670 --> 00:12:36,630
How dare you two treat an assemblyman in this way?

132
00:12:36,630 --> 00:12:39,350
Chairman Ha, do you know what time it is now?

133
00:12:39,350 --> 00:12:41,980
Let us go home already!

134
00:12:41,980 --> 00:12:47,170
All the people in here are well known enough to be recognized simply by their names.

135
00:12:47,170 --> 00:12:50,720
You shouldn't worry about any of us running away. And we're happy to answer any—

136
00:12:50,720 --> 00:12:53,100
A child!

137
00:12:54,350 --> 00:12:56,760
A child was hurt.

138
00:12:56,760 --> 00:13:00,490
She is on the brink of death right at this moment.

139
00:13:00,490 --> 00:13:02,910
I'm going to catch the culprit myself.

140
00:13:02,910 --> 00:13:07,150
Whoever that may be, I'll pursue them till the end.

141
00:13:07,150 --> 00:13:10,020
I'll bring them to the justice they deserve.

142
00:13:10,020 --> 00:13:16,150
Not even a single ant can take one foot out of this room without an alibi.

143
00:13:16,150 --> 00:13:20,420
So I advise you all to cooperate as best as you can.

144
00:13:22,850 --> 00:13:28,070
I'd been in my seat in the auditorium since the moment the Festival began.

145
00:13:28,070 --> 00:13:32,380
I only went to the bathroom once. You can verify that with the people here.

146
00:13:32,380 --> 00:13:37,440
I, too, was seated  in the same row as my husband the whole time.

147
00:13:37,440 --> 00:13:39,980
I heard you arrived first at the scene, Chairman Ju.

148
00:13:39,980 --> 00:13:42,410
Is being fast a crime too?

149
00:13:42,410 --> 00:13:47,530
And strictly speaking, it was the security guard who first came to the scene.

150
00:13:47,530 --> 00:13:49,850
I ran there after I heard Security Guard Park screaming.

151
00:13:49,850 --> 00:13:51,380
Every single one of us

152
00:13:51,400 --> 00:13:54,300
saw each other in the auditorium. Am I right or what?

153
00:13:54,300 --> 00:13:57,400
- Yes, that's true. 
- We even drank coffee together while the judges made their decisions, right?

154
00:13:57,400 --> 00:13:59,180
- Yes. 
- We were together to the end.

155
00:13:59,180 --> 00:14:03,320
Je Ni said Eun Byeol was nowhere to be seen in the waiting room.

156
00:14:03,320 --> 00:14:06,840
Shouldn't you be looking into that first?

157
00:14:06,840 --> 00:14:11,470
Now that I think about it, why haven't we seen Eun Byeol since earlier?

158
00:14:11,470 --> 00:14:13,990
I didn't see her in the athletic field, either.

159
00:14:13,990 --> 00:14:17,790
Eun Byeol wasn't feeling well, so she went home early.

160
00:14:17,790 --> 00:14:19,310
Did you say she went home?

161
00:14:19,310 --> 00:14:21,380
Did she go home without hearing who the grand prize winner was?

162
00:14:21,380 --> 00:14:23,510
That doesn't sound like Eun Byeol.

163
00:14:23,510 --> 00:14:28,460
She was a strong contender for the grand prize. She wouldn't have left even if she fainted.

164
00:14:28,460 --> 00:14:32,690
I sure hope Eun Byeol didn't take her medicine on a day like today.

165
00:14:32,690 --> 00:14:36,650
You all know Eun Byeol depends on the power of her medicine every time she performs, right?

166
00:14:36,650 --> 00:14:39,640
She wasn't feeling well because of her nerves.

167
00:14:39,640 --> 00:14:43,610
Don't tell me. Are you suspecting my  Eun Byeol?

168
00:14:43,610 --> 00:14:45,640
No one should be ruled out.

169
00:14:45,640 --> 00:14:48,740
Neither you, Ms. Cheon nor Eun Byeol.

170
00:14:48,740 --> 00:14:50,440
Don't worry.

171
00:14:50,440 --> 00:14:54,670
I'll check on Eun Byeol the moment I get home and have her undergo the questioning herself.

172
00:14:56,620 --> 00:15:00,970
Your daughter, Eun Byeol, too.

173
00:15:00,970 --> 00:15:03,190
Are you happy now?

174
00:15:03,190 --> 00:15:07,640
Let's get the people with clean alibis go home first.

175
00:15:07,640 --> 00:15:09,130
 No Entry 

176
00:15:11,820 --> 00:15:15,520
It's the wing that came off the trophy which is the suspected weapon of the crime.

177
00:15:15,520 --> 00:15:16,880
Did you say a trophy?

178
00:15:16,880 --> 00:15:19,700
The victim had the marks of getting hit by a trophy once each on her shoulder and head.

179
00:15:19,700 --> 00:15:23,320
Most of the blood loss occurred especially in her head wound.

180
00:15:23,320 --> 00:15:25,130
Where is the rest of the trophy?

181
00:15:25,130 --> 00:15:27,550
We were unable to find the rest of the trophy at the crime scene.

182
00:15:27,550 --> 00:15:31,210
As a priority, we'll zero in on locating the crime weapon that's missing for now.

183
00:15:31,210 --> 00:15:35,050
And I suggest closing the school for the time being.

184
00:15:35,050 --> 00:15:39,100
With the authority I have as a chairperson, I'll do my best to cooperate.

185
00:15:39,100 --> 00:15:44,490
Do you happen to know if anyone in school was on bad terms with the victim?

186
00:15:44,490 --> 00:15:48,150
Seeing they deliberately set off a false fire alarm to remove the evidence,

187
00:15:48,150 --> 00:15:51,290
I suspect it was someone who knew the school fairly well.

188
00:15:51,290 --> 00:15:54,650
Is there anyone that comes to your mind?

189
00:15:54,650 --> 00:15:58,230
How little do you think of  the great  Cheong Ah Arts School to say a thing like that?

190
00:15:58,230 --> 00:16:00,900
Are you implying we might have tampered with the crime scene?

191
00:16:00,900 --> 00:16:04,970
Nothing like that necessarily.

192
00:16:04,970 --> 00:16:07,190
At any event, I ask for your cooperation.

193
00:16:07,190 --> 00:16:09,080
We will.

194
00:16:12,050 --> 00:16:13,820
Why are you being so sharp?

195
00:16:13,820 --> 00:16:17,020
Do you really keep this up? Are you a cop or something?

196
00:16:17,020 --> 00:16:18,820
Or are you Bae Ro Na's real dad?

197
00:16:18,820 --> 00:16:21,840
Fine, make sure you find the culprit for Bae Ro Na's sake.

198
00:16:21,840 --> 00:16:25,380
Spend all night searching high and low.

199
00:16:40,240 --> 00:16:42,340
 Restricted Entry 

200
00:17:09,210 --> 00:17:11,320
It belongs to Ro Na.

201
00:17:15,340 --> 00:17:17,980
How is she? Did she wake up?

202
00:17:31,950 --> 00:17:36,170
Are you  Bae Ro Na's guardian? The patient just woke up.

203
00:17:57,560 --> 00:17:59,420
Ro Na?

204
00:17:59,420 --> 00:18:01,620
Ro Na, it's Mom.

205
00:18:01,620 --> 00:18:03,920
Come on, open your eyes.

206
00:18:03,920 --> 00:18:07,830
Ro Na? Ro Na, Mom's here.

207
00:18:11,960 --> 00:18:14,150
It's me, your mom. Can you recognize me?

208
00:18:14,150 --> 00:18:16,630
Ro Na?

209
00:18:16,630 --> 00:18:21,550
Who did this to you? Just who on earth did this to you?

210
00:18:22,510 --> 00:18:24,480
Ro Na.

211
00:18:26,380 --> 00:18:30,520
This is yours. You won the grand prize, Ro Na.

212
00:18:31,470 --> 00:18:35,320
Hurry, you should get up soon and celebrate with me.

213
00:18:37,090 --> 00:18:39,530
Be strong, Sweetheart. Okay?

214
00:18:39,530 --> 00:18:42,290
Be strong. You can do this.

215
00:18:42,290 --> 00:18:44,880
 It belongs to Min Seol Ah. 

216
00:18:44,880 --> 00:18:49,300
 Give that trophy to Seol Ah. 

217
00:18:49,300 --> 00:18:54,120
 I was so mean to you this whole time. 

218
00:18:54,120 --> 00:18:55,990
 For that, I'm sorry. 

219
00:18:58,610 --> 00:19:00,250
Ro Na?

220
00:19:03,050 --> 00:19:05,620
Ro Na? Ro Na, wake up!

221
00:19:05,620 --> 00:19:08,990
Ro Na! Ro Na! Ro Na! Ro Na!

222
00:19:08,990 --> 00:19:11,630
Hello? Hello!

223
00:19:11,630 --> 00:19:14,250
Somebody! Somebody, come quick!

224
00:19:14,250 --> 00:19:17,300
Ro Na! Please wake up. Please don't die!

225
00:19:17,300 --> 00:19:20,110
Ro Na! Mommy's here, Ro Na, please!

226
00:19:20,110 --> 00:19:22,730
Ro Na, don't die!

227
00:19:22,730 --> 00:19:25,640
Don't die! No, no!

228
00:19:25,640 --> 00:19:27,530
- Ro Na! Don't leave me behind!
 -  I'm going to work on her.

229
00:19:27,530 --> 00:19:32,050
It's my fault.  I must have been crazy.  I don't want anything.

230
00:19:32,050 --> 00:19:33,440
Doctor!

231
00:19:33,440 --> 00:19:36,190
- Yun Hui! 
- No! No!

232
00:19:36,190 --> 00:19:38,070
Madam!

233
00:19:38,070 --> 00:19:40,940
Ro Na! Ro Na! Don't die!

234
00:19:40,940 --> 00:19:45,210
 Ro Na! Don't go! Mommy's sorry! 

235
00:19:45,210 --> 00:19:47,240
200 joules, charge!

236
00:19:47,240 --> 00:19:48,860
Ro Na! It's my fault.

237
00:19:48,860 --> 00:19:53,000
No! Ro Na! No!

238
00:20:15,490 --> 00:20:17,360
Why are you still up?

239
00:20:20,520 --> 00:20:22,560
I had something to ask you.

240
00:20:23,660 --> 00:20:25,210
About Ro Na,

241
00:20:26,490 --> 00:20:28,860
did you do that to her?

242
00:20:28,860 --> 00:20:30,900
What are you talking about now?

243
00:20:30,900 --> 00:20:32,940
Why would I do such a thing?

244
00:20:34,240 --> 00:20:36,950
Don't lie to me.

245
00:20:36,950 --> 00:20:39,880
You had something to do with it, I'm sure.

246
00:20:39,880 --> 00:20:42,980
When Min Seol Ah died, and even when Mom died, you acted as though nothing happened just as you do now.

247
00:20:42,980 --> 00:20:46,150
Nevertheless, I know.

248
00:20:47,290 --> 00:20:49,890
That both Mom and Min Seol Ah,

249
00:20:51,040 --> 00:20:53,430
you killed them.

250
00:20:54,960 --> 00:20:56,540
My mom!

251
00:20:56,540 --> 00:20:58,030
Why did you kill her? Why?

252
00:20:58,030 --> 00:21:00,420
Because you wanted to marry someone like her?

253
00:21:00,420 --> 00:21:04,040
Or because she was Min Seol Ah's real mom?

254
00:21:04,040 --> 00:21:09,220
By any chance, if you're doing something bad to harm Ro Na—

255
00:21:09,220 --> 00:21:13,220
I never would've thought my son created such a ridiculous fantasy in his head.

256
00:21:13,220 --> 00:21:15,860
How dare you speak that kind of bullshit to me?

257
00:21:15,860 --> 00:21:18,350
Take your hands off of him!

258
00:21:20,340 --> 00:21:23,600
Neither my brother, nor am I a thing for you. You have no business beating us!

259
00:21:23,600 --> 00:21:28,350
Good timing. I had something to ask you.

260
00:21:30,830 --> 00:21:33,890
Do you know whose necklace this is?

261
00:21:33,890 --> 00:21:35,890
It's Eun Byeol's.

262
00:21:35,890 --> 00:21:38,630
She had it on earlier when she was singing.

263
00:21:40,760 --> 00:21:43,090
Why on earth do you have that with you?

264
00:21:44,840 --> 00:21:47,680
It was on the floor in the auditorium.

265
00:21:47,680 --> 00:21:49,890
You two, go to bed.

266
00:22:06,120 --> 00:22:08,100
 Don't touch a thing. 

267
00:22:08,100 --> 00:22:10,760
 Anything can be evidence. 

268
00:22:10,760 --> 00:22:14,560
 - Assemblyman— 
- When you know I'm an assemblyman, do your job right! 

269
00:22:14,560 --> 00:22:18,320
 Hey, do you know how much a bundle of spinach is? 

270
00:22:22,700 --> 00:22:26,710
So, this belongs to Ha Eun Byeol, huh?

271
00:22:33,020 --> 00:22:37,000
Where is it? I'm sure I put it in here.

272
00:22:37,710 --> 00:22:39,850
Where did I lose it?

273
00:22:44,480 --> 00:22:46,560
Are you in?

274
00:22:48,310 --> 00:22:50,290
You're home late.

275
00:22:50,290 --> 00:22:54,400
Something came up. Did Eun Byeol eat dinner?

276
00:22:54,400 --> 00:22:57,880
She didn't eat. She washed up and went to sleep as soon as she came home.

277
00:22:57,880 --> 00:23:03,010
Probably she didn't have an appetite because she was too tired. It's late, go to bed.

278
00:23:03,010 --> 00:23:08,190
Anyhow, I don't see Eun Byeol's dress.

279
00:23:08,190 --> 00:23:11,790
I'm sure she had it on when she came home, but it's not in her closet.

280
00:23:11,790 --> 00:23:17,170
She must've put it somewhere! How's that important this late in the night?

281
00:23:17,170 --> 00:23:20,330
Right. Get some rest.

282
00:23:26,350 --> 00:23:28,130
No way.

283
00:23:29,810 --> 00:23:33,830
It can't be my Eun Byeol.

284
00:23:34,740 --> 00:23:37,290
It can never be her.

285
00:23:47,780 --> 00:23:51,720
Director Do, how is Bae Ro Na?

286
00:23:53,340 --> 00:23:55,580
What?

287
00:23:55,580 --> 00:23:59,950
Are you sure there is no chance of her waking up?

288
00:25:01,970 --> 00:25:03,720
Really...

289
00:25:06,220 --> 00:25:08,470
Did you do that?

290
00:25:08,470 --> 00:25:13,970
What are you saying? I was throwing it away because I was mad that I didn't get the grand prize.

291
00:25:13,970 --> 00:25:17,130
Then what is this? The blood on the dress?

292
00:25:19,830 --> 00:25:25,220
Tell me everything. Don't leave a single thing out. What did you do to Ro Na?

293
00:25:25,780 --> 00:25:30,250
Is Ro Na... dead?

294
00:25:30,250 --> 00:25:33,320
No, right? There's no way she would die.

295
00:25:33,320 --> 00:25:35,940
She's such a tenacious person!

296
00:25:35,940 --> 00:25:38,930
No, no. No. No.

297
00:25:38,930 --> 00:25:41,970
Get it together and answer my question!

298
00:25:41,970 --> 00:25:44,320
Did you do it?

299
00:25:44,320 --> 00:25:47,740
Tell me, Ha Eun Byeol!

300
00:25:47,740 --> 00:25:52,030
She kept taking my things.

301
00:25:52,030 --> 00:25:55,920
She was always in my sight, and worse, she badmouthed you, Mom.

302
00:25:55,920 --> 00:25:59,790
She said that you slashed her mom's throat.

303
00:25:59,790 --> 00:26:04,640
That you lost to her mom.

304
00:26:04,640 --> 00:26:08,340
But, honestly, I wasn't planning on killing her!

305
00:26:08,340 --> 00:26:11,640
That's the truth. Please believe me!

306
00:26:14,470 --> 00:26:16,650
It's ok. Just pull yourself together.

307
00:26:16,650 --> 00:26:18,410
You've got to get it together, Eun Byeol!

308
00:26:18,410 --> 00:26:20,310
Calm down.

309
00:26:26,330 --> 00:26:29,640
It's all over.

310
00:26:29,640 --> 00:26:32,560
I'm a criminal.

311
00:26:32,560 --> 00:26:35,780
Probably the police will soon come for me, right?

312
00:26:38,150 --> 00:26:42,630
No. I want to go to the police station myself and tell them everything.

313
00:26:42,630 --> 00:26:45,640
That I did it.

314
00:26:45,640 --> 00:26:50,100
College or singing, it's all over for me now!

315
00:26:50,100 --> 00:26:53,380
Hey, I won't let your life messed up. Never!

316
00:26:53,380 --> 00:26:57,500
I won't allow it! I, your mother will protect you.

317
00:26:57,500 --> 00:26:59,240
Whether Bae Ro Na lives or dies,

318
00:26:59,240 --> 00:27:04,060
that's not important. You just need to keep yourself not connected to the incident.

319
00:27:04,060 --> 00:27:08,700
If anyone asks, just say you don't know anything. Understand me?

320
00:27:08,700 --> 00:27:11,800
What if someone saw me?

321
00:27:11,800 --> 00:27:15,800
The CCTVs are all over the school!

322
00:27:17,290 --> 00:27:21,610
I'll take care of it. You don't have to worry about anything.

323
00:27:24,850 --> 00:27:27,560
I'll get rid of this dress too.

324
00:27:27,560 --> 00:27:31,800
Then all is fine. There will be no evidence.

325
00:27:31,800 --> 00:27:33,530
The trophy.

326
00:27:36,390 --> 00:27:37,880
Trophy?

327
00:27:37,880 --> 00:27:42,210
Your trophy for the Cheong Ah Arts Festival.

328
00:27:43,130 --> 00:27:45,430
Where did you put it?

329
00:27:46,890 --> 00:27:49,230
In my locker.

330
00:27:49,230 --> 00:27:50,870
What?

